                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The North Atlantic Council, at the conclusion of its seventh session held in
                    Ottawa, Canada, September 15–20, 1951, agreed to the inclusion of Greece and
                    Turkey in the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.</p>
                <p>For documentation regarding the inclusion of Greece and Turkey, see <ref
                        target="frus1951v03p1#pg_460">volume III, part 1, pages 460</ref> ff. and
                        <ref target="frus1951v03p1#pg_616">616</ref> ff.</p>
                <p>The Protocol to the North Atlantic Treaty admitting Greece and Turkey to
                    membership in the Organization was signed on October 17, 1951. It is printed in
                        <hi rend="italic">Documents</hi> (R.I.I.A.) for 1951, page 65.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
